data.description: Reading like new construction yet ready to move into NOW, this gorgeous 6 bed | 6 bath home offers more upgrades than today’s discerning buyer could possibly want. Located in coveted Castle Pines, 6671 Kenzie Circle exemplifies nothing less than the best inside and out including an open concept floor plan, abundance of natural light, and equally desirable indoor | outdoor living spaces. Accessed through a 2-story entry, the main level features a great room with linear gas fireplace and herringbone patterned tile surround. The chef’s kitchen includes a large island with quartz counters, $10,000 Bertazzoni 6-burner range, stainless steel ovens, LG ThinQ fridge, and custom, organized pantry. The breakfast nook opens to a sizable back deck overlooking the professionally landscaped, lighted, and fenced back yard. Completing the main level are a large dining room with custom wainscoting, rare en suite bedroom or office, powder room, and a 3-car garage with epoxy floor and EV outlet. The upper level features an incredible owner’s suite and bathroom and custom designed walk-in closet. 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, a loft that may be converted to a bonus room, and a laundry room complete the upper level. The lower level offers a large recreation room with full wet bar including quartz bar top seating, beverage fridge, media space, recreation area, workout nook, walk-out access to lower covered stamp concrete patio, fire pit, and yard, an additional bedroom and bathroom. 2020 furnace and A/C units, water softener, and Culligan water filter. Additional owner upgrades to this impeccably maintained home include automated blinds, plantation shutters, custom organized closets, statement-making interior light fixtures, bedroom fans, exterior lighting, and landscaping enhancements. 1-minute walk to local pocket park, 5-minute drive to American Academy, DCS Montessori, Buffalo Ridge Elementary, and equidistant to a wealth of restaurants and amenities, this home simply has it all!
